AMERICAN TELEPHONE AND TELEGRAPH COMPANY, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. FLORIDA-TEXAS FREIGHT, INC., Defendant-Appellant. No. 73-2425

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 12, 1973. Richard P. Kenney, Miami, Fla., for defendant-appellant. Sherryll M. Dunaj, Miami, Fla., for plaintiff-appellee.

Before WISDOM, AINSWORTH and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir.; see Isbell Enterprses, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5 Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

For reasons cogently expressed in the district court opinion, 357 F.Supp. 977 (1973), we affirm.

Affirmed.
